{"type":"message","id":"50d0946a","parentId":"bc4de890","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:04:06.315Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"没有找到 OPENAI_API_KEY。让我检查一下 clawdbot.json 或者其他配置文件中是否有这个 key。或者我可以尝试使用其他免费的服务，比如 free-groq-voice 技能。\n\n让我检查 free-groq-voice 技能。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_921763724b1249eb9e59bc5d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/skills/free-groq-voice/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-llm-chudian-site","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":769,"output":81,"cacheRead":35008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35858,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774526638788,"responseId":"b3dd197e2477431a97a9f91f33e59a3d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"65cd4986","parentId":"50d0946a","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:04:06.322Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_921763724b1249eb9e59bc5d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: free-groq-voice\ndescription: FREE voice recognition using Groq's complimentary Whisper API. Transcribe audio messages to text in 50+ languages at no cost. Perfect for voice-to-text automation, meeting transcriptions, and accessibility features. Requires free Groq API key.\n---\n\n# Free Groq Voice Recognition\n\n## Overview\n\n**100% FREE** voice recognition powered by Groq's complimentary Whisper API (whisper-large-v3 model). No credit card required, no usage limits.\n\nConvert audio messages, voice notes, and recordings to text in 50+ languages. Perfect for:\n- 🎙️ Voice message transcription\n- 📝 Meeting notes\n- ♿ Accessibility features\n- 🤖 Voice-controlled automation\n\n## Cost: $0.00\n\n- ✅ **Completely free** Groq API tier\n- ✅ No credit card needed\n- ✅ No monthly fees\n- ✅ Generous rate limits\n- ✅ Whisper-large-v3 model (most accurate)\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Get Your FREE Groq API Key\n\n1. Visit https://console.groq.com/\n2. Sign up for free (takes 30 seconds)\n3. Navigate to API Keys\n4. Create a new API key\n5. Copy the key\n\n**That's it! No payment required.**\n\n### 2. Configure Proxy (If in Restricted Regions)\n\nGroq API may require a proxy in certain regions (e.g., mainland China).\n\n**Add to your TOOLS.md:**\n```markdown\n### Proxy Settings\n- HTTP Proxy: http://127.0.0.1:7890\n\n### Voice Recognition (FREE Groq Whisper)\n- API Key: gsk_your_key_here\n- Model: whisper-large-v3\n- Language: zh (or your preferred language)\n- Requires Proxy: Yes (if in restricted region)\n```\n\n### 3. Test the Skill\n\nSend a voice message and ask me to transcribe it!\n\n## Usage Examples\n\n**Basic Transcription:**\n```\nUser: [sends voice message]\nYou: You said: \"你好，这是一条测试消息\"\n```\n\n**With Language Hint:**\n```\nUser: 识别这段英文语音\nYou: [automatically uses language=en]\n```\n\n**Batch Processing:**\n```\nUser: 帮我识别这个文件夹里所有的语音文件\nYou: [processes all .ogg/.mp3/.wav files]\n```\n\n## Supported Languages\n\n- 🇨🇳 Chinese (zh) - Mandarin, Cantonese\n- 🇺🇸 English (en) - US, UK, Australian\n- 🇯🇵 Japanese (ja)\n- 🇰🇷 Korean (ko)\n- 🇫🇷 French (fr)\n- 🇩🇪 German (de)\n- 🇪🇸 Spanish (es)\n- 🇮🇹 Italian (it)\n- 🇵🇹 Portuguese (pt)\n- 🇷🇺 Russian (ru)\n- ... and 40+ more\n\n## Technical Details\n\n**API Endpoint:**\n```\nhttps://api.groq.com/openai/v1/audio/transcriptions\n```\n\n**Model:** `whisper-large-v3` (OpenAI's most accurate model)\n\n**Supported Formats:**\n- OGG/OPUS (Feishu, Telegram default)\n- MP3\n- WAV\n- M4A\n- WebM\n\n**Proxy Requirements:**\n- Use HTTP proxy (not SOCKS5)\n- Default: `http://127.0.0.1:7890`\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n**❌ \"Forbidden\" Error:**\n- Check API key is valid\n- Ensure proxy is configured (if in restricted region)\n- Try HTTP proxy instead of SOCKS5\n\n**❌ \"File Not Found\":**\n- Check file path is absolute\n- Ensure file exists\n\n**❌ Slow Response:**\n- Check proxy speed\n- Groq API is usually fast (< 1s for short audio)\n\n## Privacy & Security\n\n- ✅ Audio processed by Groq's API (not stored permanently)\n- ✅ API key stored locally in your TOOLS.md\n- ✅ No data sent to third parties\n- ✅ Open-source and auditable\n\n## Why Groq?\n\n**FREE vs Paid Alternatives:**\n\n| Service | Cost | Accuracy | Speed |\n|---------|------|----------|-------|\n| **Groq (FREE)** | **$0** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ | ⚡⚡⚡⚡⚡ |\n| OpenAI Whisper | $0.006/min | ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ | ⚡⚡⚡ |\n| Google Speech | $0.006/min | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | ⚡⚡⚡⚡ |\n| AWS Transcribe | $0.024/min | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | ⚡⚡⚡ |\n\n**Groq's free tier offers:**\n- Same Whisper-large-v3 model as OpenAI\n- Faster inference (Groq's LPU chip)\n- No usage limits (fair use policy)\n- No credit card required\n\n## Contributing\n\nWant to improve this skill?\n- Fork on ClawHub\n- Submit improvements\n- Share with the community\n\n## License\n\nMIT - Free to use, modify, and distribute.\n\n---\n\n**Enjoy FREE voice recognition! 🎉**\n\nNo more paying for transcription services. Groq's complimentary API makes professional-grade speech-to-text accessible to everyone.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774526646320}}
{"type":"message","id":"97c0b783","parentId":"65cd4986","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:04:15.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"这个技能使用 Groq 的免费 API，需要 API key。让我检查一下 TOOLS.md 或者其他配置中是否有 Groq API key。或者我可以尝试直接询问用户语音内容，或者使用 Python 脚本来处理。\n\n实际上，让我先尝试使用 Python 来调用 Groq API 或者 OpenAI API。但首先我需要检查是否有 API key 配置。\n\n让我先读取 TOOLS.md 看看有没有配置。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-f9e431a71581411e94c643b5501d289a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\LWS\\.openclaw\\workspace-my_work_robot\\TOOLS.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool-5e9b261554cc4913b71de240ef7ba757","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python --version 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-llm-chudian-site","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":1872,"output":218,"cacheRead":35327,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":37417,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774526646323,"responseId":"chatcmpl-7c4d7f12-48a3-97dc-8e07-72a2a14bcfb7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5897bb84","parentId":"97c0b783","timestamp":"2026-03-26T12:04:15.450Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool-f9e431a71581411e94c643b5501d289a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md - Local Notes\n\nSkills define _how_ tools work. This file is for _your_ specifics — the stuff that's unique to your setup.\n\n## What Goes Here\n\nThings like:\n\n- Camera names and locations\n- SSH hosts and aliases\n- Preferred voices for TTS\n- Speaker/room names\n- Device nicknames\n- Anything environment-specific\n\n## Examples\n\n```markdown\n### Cameras\n\n- living-room → Main area, 180° wide angle\n- front-door → Entrance, motion-triggered\n\n### SSH\n\n- home-server → 192.168.1.100, user: admin\n\n### TTS\n\n- Preferred voice: \"Nova\" (warm, slightly British)\n- Default speaker: Kitchen HomePod\n```\n\n## Why Separate?\n\nSkills are shared. Your setup is yours. Keeping them apart means you can update skills without losing your notes, and share skills without leaking your infrastructure.\n\n---\n\nAdd whatever helps you do your job. This is your cheat sheet.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774526655449}}
